		<item>
		<title>XTREME I NEW RELEASE centre fire .17 to 204 cal</title>
		<link>https://maemoderators.co.uk/product/xtreme-i-new-release/?utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=xtreme-i-new-release</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[jason]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 29 Apr 2019 12:06:55 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid isPermaLink="false">http://maemoderators.co.uk/?post_type=product&#038;p=933</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner"><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div class="vc_tta-container" data-vc-action="collapse"><div class="vc_general vc_tta vc_tta-tabs vc_tta-color-grey vc_tta-style-classic vc_tta-shape-rounded vc_tta-spacing-1 vc_tta-tabs-position-top vc_tta-controls-align-left"><div class="vc_tta-tabs-container"><ul class="vc_tta-tabs-list"><li class="vc_tta-tab vc_active" data-vc-tab><a href="#description" data-vc-tabs data-vc-container=".vc_tta"><span class="vc_tta-title-text">Description</span></a></li><li class="vc_tta-tab" data-vc-tab><a href="#features" data-vc-tabs data-vc-container=".vc_tta"><span class="vc_tta-title-text">Features</span></a></li></ul></div><div class="vc_tta-panels-container"><div class="vc_tta-panels"><div class="vc_tta-panel vc_active description" id="description" data-vc-content=".vc_tta-panel-body"><div class="vc_tta-panel-heading"><h4 class="vc_tta-panel-title"><a href="#description" data-vc-accordion data-vc-container=".vc_tta-container"><span class="vc_tta-title-text">Description</span></a></h4></div><div class="vc_tta-panel-body">
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p>The Xtreme I is our latest advancement in an over-barrel design. We have produced a “T” series over-barrel model weighing only 16.08oz (456gms), 1 1/2″ (38.1mm) diameter and an overall length of only 6.65″ (169mm), improved performance and the Sound Pressure Level (SPL) falling below 140 dB.</p>
<p>This model has increased free-bore boost for the shooter looking for increased down-range performance. The internal geometry is designed to harness the energy of the gun-shot to keep the moderator tight against the thread shoulder. 2014 will see the Xtreme range of products expanding to accommodate the larger calibres up to 458 Win Magnum.</p>
<p>The Xtreme I is designed to accept .17 HMR and .22 WMR and including 223 Rem bolt-action rifles, with barrel diameters up to 0.906″ (23.0mm).</p>

		</div>
	</div>
</div></div><div class="vc_tta-panel features" id="features" data-vc-content=".vc_tta-panel-body"><div class="vc_tta-panel-heading"><h4 class="vc_tta-panel-title"><a href="#features" data-vc-accordion data-vc-container=".vc_tta-container"><span class="vc_tta-title-text">Features</span></a></h4></div><div class="vc_tta-panel-body">
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<ol>
<li>Sound Pressure Level (SPL) below 140 dBC Linear Peak (85 dBA), to as low as 130 dBC.</li>
<li>This design has a sealed expansion chamber which comes back over the barrel allowing for better weight distribution with dual barrel contact points resulting in optimum accuracy due to controlled barrel harmonics during firing.</li>
<li>The threaded muzzle of the barrel winds into a barrel support spider located behind the groove seen on the outer tube. This aligns the muzzle to the bore of the moderator.</li>
<li>Located at the rear of the moderator is a synthetic bush which creates a secondary support on the exterior of the rifle barrel.</li>
<li>5,000x round minimum service life (approx. life of a standard rifle barrel).</li>
<li>Constructed using only quality corrosion resistant materials, with high resistance to flame degradation, retaining structual integrity.</li>
<li>High corrosion resistance to salt water exposure.</li>
<li>Internal geometry harnesses the energy of the gun-shot to keep the moderator tight on the thread shoulder, resulting in high level rifle accuracy and longevity of the product, eliminating the problems with a moderator unwinding leading to baffle strike.</li>
<li>Minimal blow-back from ejector port on firing (direct-gas semi-auto rifles only).</li>
<li>Shrink fit assembly and welded construction developed to resist high impact and abrasion.</li>
<li>Reduced muzzle flash.</li>
<li>Reduced recoil for improved target aquisition.</li>
<li><strong>Warranty: </strong>3 years</li>
</ol>

		</div>
	</div>
</div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
